      text: "<p>This seems like an odd move that I would have expected investors in GitHub to oppose for the sake of preserving one of GitHub’s biggest advantages: its large number of projects (to the point where it seems like practically everything is on GitHub).</p><p>You see, whether or not it’s justified, some projects invariably <i>will leave GitHub</i> simply <i>because it’s Microsoft</i>.  And then, GitHub will no longer feel like a place where most projects exist.  And really, GitHub isn’t perfect: projects overlook a lot of minor imperfections in GitHub’s actual product <i>because</i> there are so many projects on GitHub and the usefulness of the networking outweighs the warts here and there.</p>",
