                  type: "comment",
                  author: "acidburnNSA",
                  title: null,
                  url: null,
                  text: "<p>I could envision pre-configured vps images maintained in the open by volunteers to make it more practical. They could have unattended-upgrades configured for major patching and the community could help migrate between major LTS releases.</p><p>It isn&#x27;t ideal but it might be doable at least for some projects. Maybe devops people want new ways to contribute to open source too!</p>",
