                                              title: null,
                                              url: null,
                                              text: '<p>But they don&#x27;t really need to fix it. Sure, it&#x27;d be nice, but they&#x27;re targeting developer machines and utilities with WSL, not a server replacement of Linux. Nobody would buy a Windows license just to serve from LAMP stacks on WSL over Azure or something. Speed requirements for dev machines are a little less stringent, and as long as they are hitting better-than-Docker numbers, they will still be providing value.</p><p>Sidenote: looks like I&#x2F;O performance is really not that bad in most cases already, and sometimes even faster than Linux distros like Ubuntu: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.phoronix.com&#x2F;scan.php?page=article&amp;item=wsl-february-2018&amp;num=1" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.phoronix.com&#x2F;scan.php?page=article&amp;item=wsl-febr...</a></p>',
