                                      title: null,
                                      url: null,
                                      text: "<p>Delphi might be a small community compared to JVM or MS. Is Delphi dying?</p><p>I work in the M&#x2F;Mumps space(healthcare), another small (almost invisible) but active community and it seems far from dying. I imagine Delphi is bigger.</p><p>I wonder how long the MS stack would last without the support of MS. Would the MS stack fare as well as the Ruby stack has without Microsoft’s massive investment in turning developers into sharecroppers? (Or salesforce, scala, unreal, php, erlang, etc.)</p>",
                                      points: null,
