                                          type: "comment",
                                          author: "AnIdiotOnTheNet",
                                          title: null,
                                          url: null,
                                          text: '<p>Ads are definitely present in Pro. Perhaps you&#x27;re just not calling them ads. In the start menu you get &quot;recommended apps&quot;, explorer pops up &quot;recommendations&quot; for OneDrive, and when you switch your default browser to Chrome it nags you that you should really give Edge a chance, to name a few things people are referring to when they talk about Windows 10 having ads.</p><p>Fortunately, there&#x27;s free third party software that fix a lot of Microsoft&#x27;s bullshit: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.oo-software.com&#x2F;en&#x2F;shutup10" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.oo-software.com&#x2F;en&#x2F;shutup10</a>.</p>',
