                      created_at_i: 1528065047,
                      type: "comment",
                      author: "giancarlostoro",
                      title: null,
                      url: null,
                      text: "<p>This is in regards to one Microsoft product: Windows. Reality is, they&#x27;re not focused on Windows anymore, but I do agree it would be nice if they took away all that telemetry nonsense and allowed people to have better control over updates. To be completely fair under Linux I get updates weekly more or less, but they&#x27;re just not forced upon me to install them.</p>",
