                              created_at_i: 1528069998,
                              type: "comment",
                              author: "mchahn",
                              title: null,
                              url: null,
                              text: "<p>&gt;  in many years my amount of downtime due to Debian&#x27;s unattended-upgrades is exactly 0. The same cannot be said of Windows updates.</p><p>A few years ago I turned on my windows machine to see the dreaded upgrade.  Being in a rush I went to another machine and the exact thing happened.  I blew my top and replaced all windows with Ubuntu.  I would have preferred Macs but I couldn&#x27;t afford the Apple tax (high prices and not working on my existing HW).</p>",
                              points: null,
