                                  text: "<p>Not at all, they are supporting the model of TFS corporate deployments and generic (but embraced and extended) Git clients.</p><p>There&#x27;s an increased chance of Microsoft starting to  behave like they own Git, and trying to make it a part of their &quot;platform&quot; with proprietary extensions like their Git filesystem hack.</p>",
