                              url: null,
                              text: '<p>Uhhhh your doing this backwards. Prove that google is protecting my privacy not the other way around.</p><p>The default state for people needs to be DISTRUST of corporations (and governments) that they do not have a direct financial relationship with (when you aren&#x27;t giving them cash).</p><p>I don&#x27;t think that much of this holds water but it exists and the picture isn&#x27;t one of &quot;were standing up to defend your privacy&quot; <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;Privacy_concerns_regarding_Google" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;Privacy_concerns_regarding_Goo...</a></p>',
