                      text: "<p>I created RhodeCode, and know for sure Kallithea does not support SVN.</p><p>- RhodeCode is based on newer and more modern than turgobears2 framework, called Pyramid.</p><p>- RhodeCode had 20 releases since 2017, Kallithea had two.</p><p>- RhodeCode fixed many security issues that Kallithea didn&#x27;t, not to mention dozen of features that RhodeCode has but Kallithea doesn&#x27;t, e.g pull requests updates, integrations framework</p><p>How is that a better activity and release?</p>",
