                              author: "tannhaeuser",
                              title: null,
                              url: null,
                              text: "<p>You don&#x27;t need prayers to ensure you can continue to run your software. It&#x27;s unrealistic Linux can ever change to a different license than GPL2. Note, however, that this hasn&#x27;t stopped Linux from being used as giant spyware (Android) and being overtaken by a single entity (RedHat) slowly eroding it (Systemd, Docker).</p><p>If you&#x27;re concerned, I&#x27;d recommend basing your software on POSIX and make it also run on the BSDs, rather than just Linux, and in particular avoiding Linuxisms such as Docker and Systemd which you&#x27;ll find are poorly designed anyway.</p>",
