              created_at_i: 1528108581,
              type: "comment",
              author: "EnderMB",
              title: null,
              url: null,
              text: "<p>I guess it depends what side of Microsoft we get working with GitHub, whether it&#x27;s the friendly outreach side alongside the .NET Foundation, or whether it&#x27;s the internal software team that want to integrate GitHub into internal tooling and start moving their platform onto theirs.</p><p>My dream scenario is the former, where Microsoft provide leadership to a company that&#x27;s still reeling from its own scandals, and use GitHub as a platform for promoting open-source, rather than as a way of mining their access to the open-source world to benefit their own tooling.</p>",
