                      created_at_i: 1528099131,
                      type: "comment",
                      author: "vanderZwan",
                      title: null,
                      url: null,
                      text: "<p>&gt; <i>Ya, they can’t do the same tricks they did before. You do have to wonder what new tricks they might pull though.</i></p><p>Exactly. Unless all the leaders who flourished under the <i>&quot;Embrace, Extend, Extinguish&quot;</i> regime have been fired, that attitude is still in their blood. And especially with leadership roles, I doubt that those people didn&#x27;t manage to adapt and stay employed, because those are exactly the type who can adapt to <i>appear</i> to play nice. Whether in sheep&#x27;s clothing or any other animal, I&#x27;m sure there are plenty of wolves still at MicroSoft.</p><p>TBC, I am <i>not</i> MicroSoft is evil, or that everyone working there is. They do world-class CompSci research, and I am a very happy Visual Studio, VSC and TypeScript user. But it&#x27;s a company with thousands of people, and I doubt that they have completely reformed.</p>",
                      points: null,
