                      url: null,
                      text: "<p>Github don&#x27;t control git --</p><p>&gt; Torvalds turned over maintenance on 26 July 2005 to Junio Hamano, a major contributor to the project.[25] Hamano was responsible for the 1.0 release on 21 December 2005, and remains the project&#x27;s maintainer.[26]</p><p>I&#x27;m guessing Torvalds still has a lot of control if push came to shove, so we can assume git is executively controlled by Torvalds and Hamano.</p>",
