      text: '<p>I think a couple of people will change to gitlab or alternatives because of how Microsoft was in the 90&#x27;s.</p><p>But that Microsoft has changed, I see the most what people are complaining about is telemetry that is send, for following up on their biggest product. But all companies do this ( eg. <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;techcrunch.com&#x2F;2016&#x2F;03&#x2F;28&#x2F;its-not-just-you-clicking-on-links-in-ios-9-3-can-crash-your-iphone&#x2F;" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;techcrunch.com&#x2F;2016&#x2F;03&#x2F;28&#x2F;its-not-just-you-clicking-...</a> ), also open source applications eg. Ubuntu,.. do this.</p><p>Microsoft has changed and I think they want to show it too, because I think they have more to lose if they fail with GitHub then when they succeed (with more integration for visualstudio.com probably)</p>',
