                  type: "comment",
                  author: "matthewmacleod",
                  title: null,
                  url: null,
                  text: "<p>This completely misses the forest for the trees.</p><p>I currently pay for GitHub, personally. This has the following benefits:</p><p>- Easy to collaborate with other people if I want to invite them to my projects.</p><p>- Web-based code hosting, meaning I can access my code from anywhere regardless of whether I have access to my own machine or not.</p><p>- A web interface! This is quite useful for browsing code or sharing particular snippets with others.</p><p>- Integration with third-party tools. Almost literally every code-related service that offers integration will integrate with GitHub – things like CI servers etc. for example. This means basically zero-effort setup for many other tools.</p><p>The cost to me is basically a rounding error, and the utility is great.</p>",
