                  created_at_i: 1528059623,
                  type: "comment",
                  author: "Klathmon",
                  title: null,
                  url: null,
                  text: "<p>And there are many who would say a sedan and a crossover are basically the same thing, but the devil is in the details.</p><p>Atom is extensible to a fault. A plugin can do just about everything and anything. FFS tabs are actually a plugin! While that means that performance will suffer, many (myself included) use Atom because of that insane freedom that plugins have to do what they need to do.</p><p>VSCode on the other hand is much more &quot;if you want to do X, use this API&quot;. It&#x27;s much more controlled, much more opinionated about how things &quot;should&quot; be done using VSCode as a platform.</p><p>From 30,000 ft, they are the same. But their goals and details differ, and I always prefer more choice rather than less.</p>",
                  points: null,
