      author: "simon_acca",
      title: null,
      url: null,
      text: "<p>Ask yourself and ask your dev friends, who is paying for Github?\nI personally don&#x27;t know a single person that is subscribed to it even after spending 5 years in academia and several others in the job pool. And yet every single person that I know &amp;&amp; that can code is more than acquainted with github!</p><p>Now this could be the result of a lack of business acumen on github&#x27;s part or stubborness from the users. In any case, it might be too late for github now, but I will myself conduct a review of the free services that I use regularly and reconsider pitching in, since I value independent businesses.</p><p>EDIT: looks like my experience may be atypical, that’s good!\nJust for anecdata, would you include where you live as part of your replies? In my case it’s central europe.</p>",
