      type: "comment",
      author: "ocdtrekkie",
      title: null,
      url: null,
      text: "<p>I don&#x27;t mind this, as long as the side of Microsoft which has been on GitHub so far as the side of Microsoft who ends up dealing with GitHub in the future.</p><p>But this will definitely end the concept of GitHub as a single-source place to find code. Microsoft&#x27;s competitors will likely move their code, at the least, and of course, the crowd who will never trust Microsoft will leave as well, regardless of how well they manage it.</p><p>All-in-all, I don&#x27;t think that&#x27;s a bad thing for anyone: Software shouldn&#x27;t all come from one site, and the industry was becoming far too centralized around GitHub.</p>",
      points: null,
