          type: "comment",
          author: "pritambaral",
          title: null,
          url: null,
          text: "<p>&gt; they surely don‘t want to spend a lot of money just to destroy the relationship again</p><p>The old MS — and I&#x27;m not trying to comment on how different or similar the current MS is to the old one — did indeed spend a lot of money to screw developers and the developer community, including developers who bought into the MS stack.</p><p>&gt;  but saying that Github will be ruined? We should be better than this.</p><p>I don&#x27;t think many people are worried MS will <i>ruin</i> GitHub, per se. I think what most people are worried about is that MS will change GitHub enough to inject MS-specific stuff in there.</p>",
