                  author: "nostrademons",
                  title: null,
                  url: null,
                  text: "<p>The GitHub founders likely did quite well.  They were completely bootstrapped until they took a $100M Series A from a16z in 2012 (5 years after founding), and then took a $250M Series B valuing them at $2B from a16z, Sequoia, etc. in 2015.  Figure that they gave up 12.5% in the Series B and 30% in the Series A with a 1x liquidation preference, and that they sold for $4-5B to Microsoft (it&#x27;s unlikely the VCs would allow a sale that didn&#x27;t at least double valuation since 2015).  The three founders then split ~60% of the roughly $5B, for a cool billion dollars each.</p>",
